---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Accessibility Statement | HPSC"
	description="Learn about the Home Performance Stakeholder Council's commitment to digital accessibility and how we ensure our website is usable for everyone."
	keywords="accessibility, WCAG, AODA, digital accessibility, inclusive design, HPSC"
	breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Accessibility', href: '/accessibility' }]}
>
	<div class="w-full">
		<!-- Header -->
		<div class="mb-12">
			<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Accessibility Statement</h1>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-600">Last Updated: January 2025</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Content -->
		<div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 md:p-12 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Our Commitment to Accessibility</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					The Home Performance Stakeholder Council (HPSC) is committed to ensuring digital
					accessibility for people of all abilities. We are continually improving the user
					experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards to ensure our
					website is accessible to all users, including those with disabilities.
				</p>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We believe that everyone should have equal access to information and services, regardless
					of their physical or cognitive abilities. This commitment extends to our website, digital
					communications, and online services.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Accessibility Standards</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Our website aims to conform to the following accessibility standards:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA:</strong> Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1 at Level AA
						conformance
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>AODA:</strong> Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act requirements
					</li>
					<li><strong>Section 508:</strong> U.S. federal accessibility standards</li>
					<li><strong>EN 301 549:</strong> European accessibility standard</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Accessibility Features</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We have implemented numerous features to make our website accessible:
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Navigation and Structure</h3>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Clear and consistent navigation throughout the site</li>
					<li>Skip navigation links to jump to main content</li>
					<li>Logical heading structure (H1, H2, H3, etc.)</li>
					<li>Breadcrumb navigation on all pages</li>
					<li>Descriptive page titles and headings</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Keyboard Accessibility</h3>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Full keyboard navigation support</li>
					<li>Visible focus indicators for all interactive elements</li>
					<li>Logical tab order throughout the site</li>
					<li>No keyboard traps</li>
					<li>Keyboard shortcuts documented where applicable</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Screen Reader Compatibility</h3>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Semantic HTML markup for proper content structure</li>
					<li>ARIA labels and descriptions where needed</li>
					<li>Alternative text for all meaningful images</li>
					<li>Decorative images hidden from screen readers</li>
					<li>Form labels properly associated with inputs</li>
					<li>Error messages and status updates announced</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Visual Design</h3>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Sufficient color contrast (minimum 4.5:1 for normal text)</li>
					<li>Information not conveyed by color alone</li>
					<li>Readable font sizes and clear typography</li>
					<li>Responsive design that works at different zoom levels</li>
					<li>Support for high contrast mode</li>
					<li>No content that flashes more than 3 times per second</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Content</h3>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Plain language and clear writing</li>
					<li>Consistent and predictable design patterns</li>
					<li>Captions and transcripts for multimedia content</li>
					<li>Forms with clear labels and error messages</li>
					<li>Sufficient time to read and use content</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Assistive Technologies Supported</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Our website is designed to be compatible with the following assistive technologies:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li><strong>Screen readers:</strong> JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver, TalkBack</li>
					<li><strong>Screen magnification software:</strong> ZoomText, MAGic</li>
					<li><strong>Speech recognition software:</strong> Dragon NaturallySpeaking</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Alternative input devices:</strong> Switch controls, eye tracking, head pointers
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Browser extensions:</strong> High contrast modes, font adjusters, reading tools
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Browser and Device Compatibility</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Our website has been tested and is compatible with:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<strong>Browsers:</strong> Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge (current and previous version)
					</li>
					<li><strong>Operating Systems:</strong> Windows, macOS, iOS, Android</li>
					<li><strong>Devices:</strong> Desktop computers, laptops, tablets, smartphones</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Ongoing Efforts</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We are committed to continuous improvement of our website's accessibility:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Regular accessibility audits and testing</li>
					<li>User testing with people who use assistive technologies</li>
					<li>Staff training on accessibility best practices</li>
					<li>Incorporating accessibility into our development process</li>
					<li>Monitoring and implementing new accessibility standards</li>
					<li>Addressing feedback and issues promptly</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Known Limitations</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					While we strive for full accessibility, we acknowledge the following current limitations:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Some third-party embedded content (videos, maps) may have limited accessibility</li>
					<li>
						Legacy PDF documents may not be fully accessible (we are working to remediate these)
					</li>
					<li>Some complex interactive features are under continuous improvement</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We are actively working to address these limitations and welcome your feedback.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Third-Party Content</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Our website may contain content from third-party sources (such as embedded videos, social
					media feeds, or external widgets). While we strive to choose accessible third-party
					services, we cannot always guarantee their accessibility. If you encounter accessibility
					issues with third-party content, please let us know.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Accessibility Tips</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Here are some ways to enhance your experience on our website:
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Adjusting Text Size</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Most browsers allow you to increase text size:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<strong>Windows/Linux:</strong> Press Ctrl and + (plus) to zoom in, Ctrl and - (minus) to
						zoom out
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Mac:</strong> Press Cmd and + (plus) to zoom in, Cmd and - (minus) to zoom out
					</li>
					<li><strong>Mobile:</strong> Use pinch-to-zoom gestures</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">High Contrast Mode</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Enable high contrast mode in your operating system settings:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li><strong>Windows:</strong> Settings &gt; Ease of Access &gt; High contrast</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Mac:</strong> System Preferences &gt; Accessibility &gt; Display &gt; Increase contrast
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Keyboard Navigation</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Navigate our website using your keyboard:</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li><strong>Tab:</strong> Move forward through interactive elements</li>
					<li><strong>Shift + Tab:</strong> Move backward through interactive elements</li>
					<li><strong>Enter:</strong> Activate links and buttons</li>
					<li><strong>Space:</strong> Toggle checkboxes and buttons</li>
					<li><strong>Arrow keys:</strong> Navigate within dropdown menus and lists</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Alternative Formats</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					If you require information from our website in an alternative format, please contact us.
					We can provide content in:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Large print</li>
					<li>Braille</li>
					<li>Audio format</li>
					<li>Plain text</li>
					<li>Accessible PDF</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We will make every effort to provide the information in your requested format within a
					reasonable timeframe.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Feedback and Contact</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website. If you encounter any
					accessibility barriers, have suggestions for improvement, or need assistance accessing our
					content, please contact us:
				</p>
				<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 mb-4">
					<p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-2">Accessibility Coordinator</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-1">Home Performance Stakeholder Council</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-1">
						Email: <a
							href="mailto:accessibility@homeperformance.ca"
							class="text-primary hover:underline">accessibility@homeperformance.ca</a>
					</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-1">Phone: 1-800-123-4567</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700">Address: Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada</p>
				</div>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					When reporting an accessibility issue, please include:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>The specific page or feature you were trying to access</li>
					<li>A description of the problem you encountered</li>
					<li>Your browser and operating system</li>
					<li>Any assistive technology you were using</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 5 business days and will work with you
					to resolve the issue.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Formal Complaints</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					If you are not satisfied with our response to your accessibility concern, you may file a
					formal complaint through:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Our internal complaint process (contact our Accessibility Coordinator)</li>
					<li>
						The <a
							href="https://www.chrc-ccdp.gc.ca/"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Canadian Human Rights Commission</a>
					</li>
					<li>
						The <a
							href="https://www.ontario.ca/page/accessibility-ontario"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA)</a
						> compliance office (for Ontario residents)
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Accessibility Resources</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Learn more about web accessibility:</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">W3C Web Accessibility Initiative (WAI)</a>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://www.canada.ca/en/government/publicservice/wellness-inclusion-diversity-public-service/diversity-inclusion-public-service/accessibility-public-service.html"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Government of Canada Accessibility Resources</a>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://www.webaim.org/"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">WebAIM (Web Accessibility In Mind)</a>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://www.a11yproject.com/"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">The A11Y Project</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
